  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The hotel offers great value for money as it is on a half board or full board basis.</p>
<p>A buffet continental breakfast with additional hot options is served between 7:30-9:30 am. A late breakfast is also served at the bar until 11am.</p>
<p>If you opt for full board, you'll have lunch included too. You'll be able to take a packed lunch with you (book the day before) or a buffet lunch is served at the hotel between 12-2pm, you can eat on the terrace when the weather is nice.</p>
<p>Après ski snacks and afternoon tea including cakes and hot drinks are served from 4:30pm to keep you going until dinner for those on full board.</p>
<p>Dinner is served in buffet style four course evening meals and is served between 7-9pm. Free water, wine and fruit juices are included and there'll be show cooking -  you can expect a variety of themed and Savoyard speciality menus each evening. Optional cheese fondue is available for €10 per person.</p>
<p>Christmas and New Year gala dinners included.</p>
<p>Free upgrade to all inclusive for departures 22nd, 29th Mar &amp; 5th Apr 25 is valid for all room types. This includes full board, fruit juice, hot drinks, a draft beer and a selection of alcoholic beers.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
