  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Double rooms on half board</strong> are 15-18m² and sleep two people. These are part of a special offer on half board only, on a first come first served basis.</p>
<p><strong>Double rooms on full board</strong> are 15-18m² and sleep two people.</p>
<p><strong>Triple rooms on full board</strong> are 15-18m² and sleep two to three people. This room can be made up as a double and one single bed, or as three single beds. Please note, a twin room may be allocated if there are only two people.</p>
<p><strong>Quad rooms on full board</strong> are 30-36m², sleep two to four people and are made up of two interconnecting twin rooms. Please note that only one twin room may be allocated if there are just two people.</p>
<p>Rooms must be taken for full occupancy in high season (Christmas, New Year, French February school holidays and Easter). </p>
<p>Free upgrade to all inclusive for departures 22nd, 29th Mar &amp; 5th Apr 25 is valid for all room types.</p>
<p><strong>Bedroom facilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Twin or double beds (please specify at time of booking)</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Bathroom with shower</li>
<li>Separate WC</li>
<li>Heated towel rail</li>
<li>Toiletries</li>
<li>Towels </li>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Linen and towels are changed on request</li>
<li>Baby cots are available for children under 2 years (free, on request)</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
